The food is spectacular! Has a "home cooked" feel to it. The service is great considering that they get slammed. The pricing is fantastic given the superb taste of the food. We were recommended to come here by the Lyft driver that brought us into the area when we came to NYC for vacation. Let's put it this way...for the next 3 days we returned for our breakfast. When you come in for breakfast ask for "Tres Golpes". It's basically a sampler of Mangu, chorizo and salami with a fried egg and sweet pickled red onions. INSTANT eyeroll at the deliciousness that occurs in your mouth! When we return to NYC this will be one of our "mom & pop" restaurants we will come to again & again! Muchas Gracias por la hospitabilidad y la comida! Y sigan tocando la musica de boleros viejos!!
